{"key":"post-6417746","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6417746</id>\n<content>I mean to do whatever is necessary to get some gas exchange going.  The vermiculite barrier is your filter, so you need holes in the lid, or you need to loosen the ring that holds the lid in place so that gasses can filter up through the vermiculite and escape around the edges of the loose lid. Self-healing injection ports are supposed to close off once you pull the needle out so air can't exchange through them. If your jars are airtight, the mycelium will stall out and die.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>6416127</prev>\n<first>6415989</first>\n<last>6417746</last>\n<when>1167759133</when>\n<utime>01/02/07 07:32 PM</utime>\n</post>"}